<section id="body">
  <p align="left"><b>1.</b>  Who do you have to write to?<g id="t1">A.  a stranger</g><g id="t2">B.  an acquaintance</g><g id="t3">C.  a colleague</g><g id="t4">D.  a relative</g><g id="t5">E.  a friend</g></p>
  <p align="left"><b>2.</b>  What style of letter should you write?<g id="t6">A.  formal</g><g id="t7">B.  informal</g></p>
  <p align="left"><b>3.</b>  What do you have to do in this letter?<g id="t8">A.  describe something</g><g id="t9">B.  offer advice</g><g id="t10">C.  give reasons</g><g id="t11">D.  make a recommendation</g><g id="t12">E.  express preferences</g></p>
  <p align="left"><b>4.</b>  How many points do you have to coverin this letter?<g id="t13">A.  one</g><g id="t14">B.  two</g><g id="t15">C.  three</g><g id="t16">D.  four</g><g id="t17">E.  five</g></p>
  <p align="left"><b>5.</b>  Which of the following would it beappropriate to write about in this letter?<g id="t18">A.  the author's life story</g><g id="t19">B.  the title of the book</g><g id="t20">C.  the name of the author</g><g id="t21">D.  the characters</g><g id="t22">E.  a review of the film version of the book</g><g id="t23">F.  the setting</g><g id="t24">G.  the plot</g></p>
